library(keyring)

# Read canvas course information
library(rcanvas)

# Data wrangling and formatting
library(tidyverse)
library(kableExtra)

# Plotting

2 Load Data and Wrangle

gb_list <- read_csv("../data/gb_list.csv")

Missing column names filled in: X1 [1] Column specification cols( X1 = col_double(), anon_id = col_character(), assignment_name = col_character(), score = col_double(), course_id = col_double(), course_name = col_character() )

gb_list <- gb_list %>% 
  mutate(course_id = as_factor(course_id)) %>% 
  mutate(course_name = as_factor(course_name))
# order the factors properly
gb_list$course_name <- factor(gb_list$course_name,
                              levels= c(
                                "ANTH-125G S19",
                                "ANTH-125G F19",
                                "HON-235G F19",
                                "ANTH-125G S20",
                                "ANTH-125G F20",
                                "HON-235G F20",
                                "ANTH-1140G S21",
                                "HNRS-2161G S21"
                              ))

3 Exam 1

# gb_list %>% 
#   filter(str_detect(assignment_name, "^Exam1|^EXAM1")) %>% 
#   group_by(course_name) %>%
#   select(assignment_name, score, course_name) %>% 
#   descr()
gb_list %>% 
  filter(str_detect(assignment_name, "^Exam1|^EXAM1")) %>% 
  group_by(course_name) %>% 
ggplot(., aes(x = score))+
  geom_histogram()+
  facet_wrap(~ course_name)+
    labs(
    title = "Exam 1 Histograms Across Classes"
  )

NA
gb_list %>% 
  group_by(course_id) %>% 
  filter(str_detect(assignment_name, "^Exam1|^EXAM1")) %>% 
  ggplot(.,aes(x=course_name, y = score, group=course_name))+
  geom_boxplot()+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))+
    labs(
    title = "Exam 1 Scores Across Different Classes",
    x = "Course",
    y = "Exam Score"
  )

gb_list %>% 
  group_by(course_name) %>% 
  filter(str_detect(assignment_name, "^Exam1|^EXAM1")) %>%
  ggbetweenstats(
    data = .,
    x = course_name,
    y = score,
    pairwise.comparisons = FALSE)+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))+
    labs(
    title = "Exam 1 Scores Across Different Classes",
    x = "Course",
    y = "Exam Score"
  )
